WEBVTT

00:00:21.030 --> 00:00:24.855
The sunshine coming through the glass windows

00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:30.166
Reflects off the blackboard, making it hard to see

00:00:31.661 --> 00:00:35.446
Nothing that really matters is written there anyway

00:00:37.076 --> 00:00:40.701
I keep on gazing at you

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:45.643
Those numbers that are lined up

00:00:46.086 --> 00:00:51.669
What meaning do they hold?

00:00:51.670 --> 00:00:56.572
Like pi that never ends

00:00:56.572 --> 00:01:02.006
I really wanted to keep on going

00:01:02.221 --> 00:01:07.560
Its infinite decimal digits

00:01:07.556 --> 00:01:12.836
As many as the loving words I want to say

00:01:13.489 --> 00:01:18.830
No matter how far, no matter how long, even to hundreds of millions of digits

00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:22.904
I can't find the solution to my feelings

00:01:34.147 --> 00:01:37.864
To have you sitting diagonally across from me

00:01:39.803 --> 00:01:43.907
Is that good luck or bad luck?

00:01:44.750 --> 00:01:48.393
Because I can't focus on the lesson

00:01:50.406 --> 00:01:54.153
But I feel happy

00:01:54.443 --> 00:01:58.978
Love is infinite

00:01:59.421 --> 00:02:04.566
This feeling of love will just go on

00:02:04.566 --> 00:02:09.704
22/7, numerator over denominator

00:02:10.153 --> 00:02:15.138
My feelings keep surfacing again and again

00:02:15.581 --> 00:02:20.486
My unresolved affection

00:02:20.769 --> 00:02:26.418
Leaves a lingering uneasiness 

00:02:26.929 --> 00:02:29.928
It won't stop, this emotion 

00:02:29.929 --> 00:02:32.153
And for me right now

00:02:32.153 --> 00:02:36.769
It's the most important thing of all

00:02:36.769 --> 00:02:41.846
How far should I go to find the answer?

00:02:42.123 --> 00:02:47.255
No one really knows

00:02:47.729 --> 00:02:52.707
My heart is in circles

00:02:52.707 --> 00:02:58.141
Endlessly thinking of you

00:03:11.458 --> 00:03:16.535
Like pi that never ends

00:03:16.535 --> 00:03:22.104
I really wanted to keep on going

00:03:22.104 --> 00:03:27.396
Its infinite decimal digits

00:03:27.396 --> 00:03:32.676
As many as the loving words I want to say

00:03:33.470 --> 00:03:38.793
No matter how far, no matter how long, even to hundreds of millions of digits

00:03:38.793 --> 00:03:43.150
I can't find the solution to my feelings

00:03:44.147 --> 00:03:48.400
"π" isn't enough to express it